dismissalText.commentary: Imad Wasim run out (Mutumbami) 61 (61b 5x4 0x6 81m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: tries to make room and Panyangara bowls it wide outside off. Leaves it, and it's called wide. They try to sneak a bye as well, and Mutumbami kicks the ball into the stumps at the batsman's end, finds Wasim short of his crease. End of a superb partnership.

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Jumped down the track, and slogged in a rather unedifying manner, across the line, his head swivelling all over the place. A touch of Javagal Srinath about that shot. Good ball from Nyumbu too, it went above the batsman's eyeline and dipped below it quickly. Snappy flight, and it turned in sharply from outside off to knock back middle stump

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalComment.html: slower ball wide outside off, and Jongwe has struck. Dangled it out there, and Hafeez took the bait, went hard at the drive, hit it too early, and the cover fielder took a good catch over his head

dismissalText.commentary: Azhar Ali run out (Nyumbu) 11 (22b 2x4 0x6 25m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Nyumbu atones for the dropped catch with a brilliant direct hit! Azhar takes a huge step down the track, and Jongwe shortens his length. He defends, and the ball runs away towards wide second slip. He didn't know where the ball had gone, and starts for a single. I think Shehzad may have said yes, and then no, and by the time Azhar turned back it was too late. Pinpoint throw from Nyumbu to catch him well short.

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad c Chigumbura b Panyangara 12 (16b 2x4 0x6 32m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: oho, that's a soft dismissal. This wasn't as full as the previous one, and he went for the drive with his hands, not too much of a front-foot stride. Spoons it straight to mid-off

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams b Shoaib Malik 26 (31b 0x4 1x6 53m) SR: 83.87

dismissalComment.html: goes for the big hit to the wrong ball and he is done in. Shakes his head and slaps his bat down on the turf in disappointment. Lulled by the flight of the ball (or lack ot) Thought he could reach the pitch. He couldnt and with him committed to playing across the line - as it happens with most sweep shots - he cannot connect and watches his middle stump take a hit

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Mohammad Rizwan b Yasir Shah 22 (30b 2x4 0x6 38m) SR: 73.33

dismissalComment.html: five-for! Another lazy little hit across the line by a Zimbabwe batsman coming down the track. Chigumbura has not reached the pitch, which means the ball has enough time to turn, take the outside edge and settle in the hands of cover

headshotImage.caption: Brian Chari player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Brian Chari player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: googly? No, just goes on with the arm. Chari has not picked it. He has, however, provided ample gap between bat and pad. Lovely bowling from Yasir, and he celebrates with a big ol smile. Chari had lunged forward looking for the one going away, as such his hands are leading away from his body. The ball though pitches and moves just enough the other way to breach his defences

stayed just a touch low, although this is more a misjudgment from the batsman. Rocked back trying to go for a pull, but it wasnt quite short enough for that. Hami M realises that and tries to save face with a straight bat. Just not quick enough. With a free passage - the batsman had backed away to enable his shot - Yasir gets the ball to crash into middle

races down the track for a huge heave over the leg side. Awful shot with his team already in trouble. More comes their way as the outside edge settles in the hands of short third man. May have just held that one back on middle to fool the charging batsman

he has four, and he owes it to the catcher! Hafeez has pulled off a stunning one-hander to his right. This was a quicker ball on off stump, Mutumbami plants an open face down on it and it seems like he has eked out an easy single using the pace of the leggie. But Hafeez has stayed low, his reflexes are still sharp and he sticks out the right hand to claim a catch he will remember for a while

five-for! Another lazy little hit across the line by a Zimbabwe batsman coming down the track. Chigumbura has not reached the pitch, which means the ball has enough time to turn, take the outside edge and settle in the hands of cover

and there it is. Zimbabwe are done. Another good length ball, which gets a little more bounce than normal. Panyangara goes for a pull, seems to have gotten a little bit of glove to pop a catch to slip

dismissalComment.html: plumb in front! Malik has been bowling a few too many down leg. This time though he has tossed the ball up just outside off, it turns rather sharply too. Hits Jonwe below the knee-roll on the pad before his bat can come down in time. Looked very bad for the batsman and it was

huge lbw appeal from the bowler, and it seems to be only him asking for it. But the ump agrees! Cremer goes for a reverse sweep. Pulled into that shot because Malik was frustrating him with darts on leg stump. Has not make any connection and is stuck on the thigh pad in front of leg stump. Considering the turn Malik is getting I am not sure that would have hit

dismissalText.commentary: Tinashe Panyangara c Imad Wasim b Yasir Shah 4 (6b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 66.66

commentTextItems.html: and there it is. Zimbabwe are done. Another good length ball, which gets a little more bounce than normal. Panyangara goes for a pull, seems to have gotten a little bit of glove to pop a catch to slip

commentPostTextItems.html: That is all we have for you here. Thanks for joining us, hope to see you again on Saturda

Yasir Shah is Man of the Match: I played my debut here, and I was happy to come back and play this way. I have been practicing very hard. There was a bit of gap, but I did not feel any difficulty coming back from the off season. I was fully confident

Azhar Ali says: As a team we have performed very well. Early on it was tough, but the partnership between Sarfraz and Malik gave us belief and Rizwan and Wasim played exceptionally well. My arm is okay [after the blow in the first over], it surprised be, I did not think the ball might have bounced as much. But I think the pitch was not coming onto the bat that well. The score we had, we were very confident of defending with the kind of spin attack we had. Imad Wasim and Yasir Shah and Shoaib Malik bowled really well

Elton Chigumbura says: They are using these conditions better than us. Especially withe spinners, the majority of the wickets were to their spinners. Just have to make sure, the next game is very important to bounce back and stay in this series

4.30 pm Hugs all around, pats on Yasir's back. Seems like every time he was given the ball he could prise a Zimbabwe batsmen out. Gets a big hug from the spin coach Mushtaq Ahmed. His 6 for 26 is the second-best figures by a Pakistan spinner ODIs, and all 10 wickets have fallen to spin. That should indicate the slowness, and the help available for the slower bowlers. Odd that Zimbabwe would play on such a surface. Odder still were some of the shots they played - Williams and Raza and Chigumbura heaving across the line.

Two hundred and fifty nine is not normally a winning score in ODI cricket right now, but Zimbabwe struggled to pose any threat to it. They wanted to take it slow early on to try and lay a strong foundation despite the mounting run-rate. But once Pakistan threw their spinners at them, Zimbabwe crumbled away.
Areeb Salman: "His 6-26 are the second-best figures for a Pak spinner in ODIs. What are the best figures? And of whom? " ---- Shahid Afridi got a seven-for against West Indies not too long ago

lifted over mid-off
another big lbw appeal as Yasir fires one in full and at leg stump. Panyangara looks to defend but he is doing it down the wrong line. Tight shout, but the umpire things that would be slipping down
premeditated the lap sweep, which gave Yasir all the warning he needed. Bowls flatter and well outside off to foil the stroke
googly, but Nyumbu seems to have picked it. Leans forward and blocks into the covers
sweep connects and how! This is a length ball and Panyangara has simply swatted it away to the square leg boundary

good length ball on off stump, defended
short and just outside off, chopped into the covers by Nyumbu

dismissalText.commentary: Azhar Ali run out (Nyumbu) 11 (22b 2x4 0x6 25m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Nyumbu atones for the dropped catch with a brilliant direct hit! Azhar takes a huge step down the track, and Jongwe shortens his length. He defends, and the ball runs away towards wide second slip. He didn't know where the ball had gone, and starts for a single. I think Shehzad may have said yes, and then no, and by the time Azhar turned back it was too late. Pinpoint throw from Nyumbu to catch him well short.

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad c Chigumbura b Panyangara 12 (16b 2x4 0x6 32m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: oho, that's a soft dismissal. This wasn't as full as the previous one, and he went for the drive with his hands, not too much of a front-foot stride. Spoons it straight to mid-off

dismissalText.commentary: Imad Wasim run out (Mutumbami) 61 (61b 5x4 0x6 81m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: tries to make room and Panyangara bowls it wide outside off. Leaves it, and it's called wide. They try to sneak a bye as well, and Mutumbami kicks the ball into the stumps at the batsman's end, finds Wasim short of his crease. End of a superb partnership.

headshotImage.longCaption: Brian Chari player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brian Chari b Yasir Shah 16 (36b 1x4 0x6 59m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: googly? No, just goes on with the arm. Chari has not picked it. He has, however, provided ample gap between bat and pad. Lovely bowling from Yasir, and he celebrates with a big ol smile. Chari had lunged forward looking for the one going away, as such his hands are leading away from his body. The ball though pitches and moves just enough the other way to breach his defences

headshotImage.caption: Imad Wasim player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Imad Wasim player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha lbw b Imad Wasim 12 (27b 2x4 0x6 37m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: strikes first ball! Went back in his crease, hoping to give himself a little more time to pick the ball away through midwicket. But the ball skids on and foils all that. Strikes him in line with the stumps, the only question might be if the ball would just carry on down leg. The umpire doesnt think so, however

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza b Yasir Shah 15 (34b 1x4 0x6 41m) SR: 44.11

dismissalComment.html: stayed just a touch low, although this is more a misjudgment from the batsman. Rocked back trying to go for a pull, but it wasnt quite short enough for that. Hami M realises that and tries to save face with a straight bat. Just not quick enough. With a free passage - the batsman had backed away to enable his shot - Yasir gets the ball to crash into middle

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams b Shoaib Malik 26 (31b 0x4 1x6 53m) SR: 83.87

dismissalComment.html: goes for the big hit to the wrong ball and he is done in. Shakes his head and slaps his bat down on the turf in disappointment. Lulled by the flight of the ball (or lack ot) Thought he could reach the pitch. He couldnt and with him committed to playing across the line - as it happens with most sweep shots - he cannot connect and watches his middle stump take a hit

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Shoaib Malik b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza c Shoaib Malik b Yasir Shah 19 (40b 1x4 0x6 51m) SR: 47.5

dismissalComment.html: races down the track for a huge heave over the leg side. Awful shot with his team already in trouble. More comes their way as the outside edge settles in the hands of short third man. May have just held that one back on middle to fool the charging batsman

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Rizwan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Rizwan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Rizwan b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Mohammad Rizwan b Yasir Shah 22 (30b 2x4 0x6 38m) SR: 73.33

dismissalComment.html: five-for! Another lazy little hit across the line by a Zimbabwe batsman coming down the track. Chigumbura has not reached the pitch, which means the ball has enough time to turn, take the outside edge and settle in the hands of cover

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Hafeez b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami c Mohammad Hafeez b Yasir Shah 3 (5b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: he has four, and he owes it to the catcher! Hafeez has pulled off a stunning one-hander to his right. This was a quicker ball on off stump, Mutumbami plants an open face down on it and it seems like he has eked out an easy single using the pace of the leggie. But Hafeez has stayed low, his reflexes are still sharp and he sticks out the right hand to claim a catch he will remember for a while

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Jongwe lbw b Shoaib Malik 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: plumb in front! Malik has been bowling a few too many down leg. This time though he has tossed the ball up just outside off, it turns rather sharply too. Hits Jonwe below the knee-roll on the pad before his bat can come down in time. Looked very bad for the batsman and it was

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer lbw b Shoaib Malik 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: huge lbw appeal from the bowler, and it seems to be only him asking for it. But the ump agrees! Cremer goes for a reverse sweep. Pulled into that shot because Malik was frustrating him with darts on leg stump. Has not make any connection and is stuck on the thigh pad in front of leg stump. Considering the turn Malik is getting I am not sure that would have hit

headshotImage.caption: Imad Wasim player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Imad Wasim player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Imad Wasim b Yasir Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Tinashe Panyangara c Imad Wasim b Yasir Shah 4 (6b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: and there it is. Zimbabwe are done. Another good length ball, which gets a little more bounce than normal. Panyangara goes for a pull, seems to have gotten a little bit of glove to pop a catch to slip
